            "body": "As I look at this a bit more, note that this is also a better way to determine the inset: Let **gmt inset** decide from the **-R -J**:\r\n\r\n```\r\ngmt begin map\r\n    gmt coast -R-74/-69.5/41/43 -JM15c -Baf -Wthin -Clightblue -Glightyellow\r\n    gmt inset begin -DjBL+o0.5c/0.2c -F+pblack+gwhite -R-80/-65/35/50 -JM3c\r\n        gmt coast -Ggray -Cwhite -EUS.MA+gred -W1/thin -N1 -N2\r\n    gmt inset end\r\ngmt end show\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere, **-D** does _not_ specify the size but we give the desired **-R -J** and now the inset is computed correctly with a tight fit.  If you dont want a width of 3c but a height of 3c then you append **+dh** to **-J**, for instance.\r\n\r\nIn the original user's case, this is the preferred way of doing things.  But, this PR is still useful since it fixes a bug.",
